=<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Welcome To GMI</title>
    <style>
        :root {
            --n8n-bg: #131416;
            --n8n-surface: #1b1c20;
            --n8n-border: #2a2c31;
            --n8n-text: #e1e1e1;
            --n8n-text-muted: #9a9a9a;
            --n8n-green: #37e2a3;
            --n8n-purple: #a45fff;
            --n8n-font: 'Inter', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
        }

        body {
            font-family: var(--n8n-font);
            background-color: var(--n8n-bg);
            color: var(--n8n-text);
            margin: 0;
            padding: 2rem;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        .container {
            max-width: 900px;
            margin: 0 auto;
        }

        .header {
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 3rem;
        }

        .header h1 {
            font-size: 2.8rem;
            font-weight: 700;
            background: -webkit-linear-gradient(45deg, var(--n8n-green), var(--n8n-purple));
            -webkit-background-clip: text;
            -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        }

        .header p {
            font-size: 1.2rem;
            color: var(--n8n-text-muted);
            max-width: 650px;
            margin: 0 auto;
        }

        .step {
            background-color: var(--n8n-surface);
            border: 1px solid var(--n8n-border);
            border-radius: 12px;
            padding: 2rem;
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
            display: flex;
            gap: 2rem;
            align-items: flex-start;
        }

        .step-number {
            flex-shrink: 0;
            width: 50px;
            height: 50px;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            border-radius: 50%;
            background-color: var(--n8n-border);
            font-size: 1.5rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            color: var(--n8n-green);
        }

        .step-content h2 {
            margin-top: 0;
            font-size: 1.5rem;
            color: var(--n8n-text);
        }

        .step-content p, .step-content ul {
            color: var(--n8n-text-muted);
        }

        .step-content ul {
            padding-left: 20px;
        }

        .step-content li {
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        }

        code {
            font-family: 'Fira Code', 'Courier New', monospace;
            background-color: var(--n8n-bg);
            color: var(--n8n-green);
            padding: 0.2em 0.4em;
            border-radius: 4px;
            font-size: 0.9em;
        }

        .code-block {
            background-color: var(--n8n-bg);
            border: 1px solid var(--n8n-border);
            border-radius: 8px;
            padding: 1.5rem;
            margin-top: 1rem;
            overflow-x: auto;
        }

        .code-block pre {
            margin: 0;
        }

        .code-block code {
            padding: 0;
            background: none;
            color: var(--n8n-text-muted);
        }

        .code-block .comment {
            color: #6a6a6a;
        }

        .final-note {
            text-align: center;
            padding: 2rem;
            background-color: var(--n8n-surface);
            border: 1px solid var(--n8n-border);
            border-radius: 12px;
        }

        .final-note h2 {
            color: var(--n8n-green);
        }

        a {
            color: var(--n8n-green);
            text-decoration: none;
            font-weight: 500;
        }

        a:hover {
            text-decoration: underline;
        }

        @media (max-width: 768px) {
            body { padding: 1rem; }
            .header h1 { font-size: 2.2rem; }
            .step { flex-direction: column; }
            .step-number { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
        }
    </style>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&family=Fira+Code&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body>

    <div class="container">

        <header class="header">
            <h1>Welcome To GMI</h1>
            <p>Learn how to use a simple n8n workflow to act as a web server, returning a complete HTML page to anyone who visits your webhook URL.</p>
        </header>

        <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">1</div>
            <div class="step-content">
                <h2>The Trigger: Webhook Node</h2>
                <p>Every workflow that responds to a web request starts with the <strong>Webhook</strong> node. This is your entry point.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Add a new Webhook node to an empty canvas.</li>
                    <li>Set the <strong>HTTP Method</strong> to <code>GET</code>. This means it will respond when someone visits the URL in their browser.</li>
                    <li>Copy the <strong>Production URL</strong>. You'll use this to see your workflow in action. Once you activate the workflow, you'll be able to see your webpage in the browser.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">2</div>
            <div class="step-content">
                <h2>The Response: Respond to Webhook Node</h2>
                <p>This is where the magic happens. This node sends your data back to the browser that triggered the webhook.</p>
                <p>Connect a <strong>Respond to Webhook</strong> node to your Webhook node. To make it serve a webpage, you need to configure two things:</p>

                <p><strong>1. Set the Content-Type Header:</strong></p>
                <p>You must tell the browser it's receiving an HTML document. Under <strong>Options</strong>, add a Response Header:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Name:</strong> <code>Content-Type</code></li>
                    <li><strong>Value:</strong> <code>text/html</code></li>
                </ul>

                <p><strong>2. Add your HTML to the Body:</strong></p>
                <p>In the <strong>Body</strong> field of the node, paste your entire HTML code. The workflow will send this exact content as the response.</p>

                <div class="code-block">
                    <pre><code><span class="comment">&lt;!-- Paste your entire HTML file here --&gt;</span>
&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html lang="fr"&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
    &lt;meta charset="UTF-8"&gt;
    &lt;title&gt;Your Very Own WebPage (AI can build it);/title&gt;
    &lt;style&gt;
        :root {
            --bg-color: #2e2e30;
            /* ... all your other CSS styles ... */
        }
        body {
            font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto;
            /* ... etc ... */
        }
    &lt;/style&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
    &lt;div class="container"&gt;
        &lt;h1&gt;üöÄ Your Very Own WebPage (AI can build it)&lt;/h1&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;You can put any html here !!&lt;/p&gt;

        &lt;!-- ... The rest of your HTML content ... --&gt;

    &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
</code></pre>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="final-note">
            <h2>That's It!</h2>
            <p>Activate your workflow. Now, when you visit your <strong>Production URL</strong>, n8n will serve your custom webpage. You've successfully turned a simple workflow into a mini web server.</p>
            <p>This method is perfect for creating landing pages, dashboards, or dynamic pages where n8n fetches data before rendering the HTML.</p>
        </div>

    </div>

</body>
</html>
